Hello,

I have noticed this bug in the Eclipse plugin for TypeScript, and the developer thinks the problem is with the getReferencesAtPosition API. The WebStorm implementation seems to have the same bug.

```
interface IFoo {
    bar();
}

class Foo implements IFoo {
    bar() {}
}
```

Renaming the bar method in IFoo does not affect the method in Foo, and vice versa. And also:

```
class Foo {
    method() {}
}

class Bar extends Foo {
    method() {}
}
```

Renaming Foo.method does not affect Bar.method, and vice versa.

This issue could possibly introduce new bugs when refactoring method names in a large project. Such a problem may even go undetected by the compiler â€“ especially for the second case.
